external_knowledge:
- 'good quality readings' refers to readings where the data quality flag is 'good';
- 'latest maintenance details' include the most recent maintenance date and description for each sensor;
- 'sensor ID' uniquely identifies each sensor in the system.

sql:
SELECT value
FROM readings
WHERE dataset_id = 0 AND reading_id IN (SELECT reading_id FROM annotations);

SELECT date
FROM readings
WHERE reading_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Top annotators" refers to users who have provided annotations;
- "Highest average reading values" means the readings with the highest average values for each sensor type;
- "Sensor types" include different types of sensors such as temperature, humidity, and pressure.

- 'Types of sensors' refer to the different kinds of sensors like temperature, humidity, pressure, etc.;
- 'Cloud of suspicion' refers to the annotations containing the word 'suspicious';
- 'Guardian of the zeroth realm' refers to the user with ID 0;
- 'Average uncertainty' is the average of the `measurement_uncertainty` column.

- 'garden of sensors' refers to a collection of sensors deployed in various locations;
- 'whisper an average moisture level' refers to the average value of humidity readings;
- 'dewy threshold of 60.0' refers to an average humidity value greater than 60.0.

- " Sensors in the vast garden of data" refers to the sensors in the database;
- "Landscape" refers to the location where the sensor is deployed;
- "Most scrutinized and frequented" refers to having more than one annotation and more than five access events;
- "Marked by more than one note" refers to the `annotation_count` being greater than 0;
- "Visited over five times" refers to the `access_count` being greater than 5.

- 'Harbingers of fresh data' refers to notifications of type 'data available';
- 'Guardians of the sensors' refers to users who receive notifications about specific sensors;
- 'Tended to' refers to sensors that have been part of maintenance activities.

- "Environmental heartbeat" refers to sensor readings;
- "City square" refers to the location with `location_id = 1`;
- "Dawn of the new year" refers to the start of 2023, i.e., January 1, 2023.

- "the heartbeat of the environment" refers to the sensor readings;
- "the mystical land of location 1001" refers to the location with `location_id = 1001`;
- "since the dawn of 2022" refers to readings taken on or after January 1, 2022;
- "in a harmonious order" means the results are ordered in ascending order.

- 'Frequent visitor' refers to a user who has accessed data more than 10 times;
- 'Wisdom scrolls' refer to the data entries in the system;
- 'Dawn of the year and its final sunset' refers to the date range from January 1, 2023, to December 31, 2023.
